			<title><![CDATA[Senior Engineer, Infrastructure]]></title>
			<department><![CDATA[Technology]]></department>
			<team><![CDATA[Technology]]></team>
			<url><![CDATA[http://bonobos.theresumator.com/apply/mxTYAZ/Senior-Engineer-Infrastructure.html]]></url>
			<city><![CDATA[New York]]></city>
			<state><![CDATA[NY]]></state>
			<country><![CDATA[United States]]></country>
			<postalcode><![CDATA[10010]]></postalcode>
			<description><![CDATA[<p>
<strong>Bonobos is searching for a Senior Engineer to help develop and operate a robust infrastructure.&nbsp;</strong></p>
<p>
At Bonobos, our systems engineers are tasked with the rapid development of new features while ensuring performance, scalability, availability and security. A robust infrastructure allows these engineers to maximize their focus developing new systems features without sacrificing quality. Your job as a senior engineer on our Infrastructure engineering team will be to help develop and operate this infrastructure. And, to have an awesome time doing it.&nbsp;</p>
<p>
To succeed in this role, you must collaborate effectively with other Bonobos engineering team members to determine their infrastructure needs and how best to deliver it. You will have a broad awareness of current and emerging technologies and their respective strengths and weaknesses for different applications. You will help perform technology assessments to evaluate technology for Bonobos&#39; specific needs. You&#39;ll make it simpler for engineers to integrate complex technology or perform repetitive tasks with tools and automation.&nbsp;</p>
<p>
<strong>You&hellip;</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Are always learning and thinking outside the box...wait, what box?</li>
<li>
Are looking to join a team that is truly engaging, fulfilling, energetic,&nbsp;quirky, sometimes weird and always passionate</li>
<li>
Are proficient in all aspects of systems engineering and have five or more years of related experience</li>
<li>
Know how to build scalable, available, high performance and scalable systems and how &nbsp;to validate those qualities</li>
<li>
May be familiar with cloud technology</li>
<li>
Are a closet bocce pro...or at least are willing to learn</li>
<li>
Can name your favorite Game of Thrones character</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>We&hellip;&nbsp;</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Value self-awareness, intellectual honesty, judgment, empathy and positive energy, often, over experience</li>
<li>
Work hard because we love what we&rsquo;re doing, but also believe in balance</li>
<li>
Will back up our talk with a competitive compensation and benefits package, challenging projects, random acts of team-wide fun, awesome co-workers and the rare tribal atmosphere that values individuality</li>
<li>
Are more inspired by opportunities than fear of failure</li>
<li>
Are willing to help you relocate</li>
<li>
Are excited to hear from you</li>
</ul>
]]></description>
