			<description><![CDATA[<p>
<b>Bonobos is looking for an experienced HR Manager to lead our HR operations while keeping our most important customers in mind: our employees.</b></p>
<p>
<span style="font-size: 12px;">Managing the HR operations of a rapidly expanding company like ours ain&#39;t easy, especially when it&#39;s historically been tasked among individuals with other responsibilities. So it&#39;s high time we bring on a dedicated HR pro who&#39;s solely responsible for implementing and running the systems and processes needed to help our business grow. In doing so, they&#39;ll provide our employees with the support they need to make working here the most rewarding, and frankly awesome, experience possible.</span></p>
<p>
This isn&#39;t just about systems, spreadsheets and reports (though yes, there&#39;s a bunch of that). This is about our most important asset - our people. From benefits administration to HRIS implementation and beyond, you&#39;ll be responsible for running the behind-the-scenes efforts that keep our company legally compliant and our employees fired up and engaged on a daily basis. At Bonobos, HR is about treating people with the utmost respect. It&#39;s about guiding them through good and occasionally challenging times. It&#39;s about navigating important and serious issues while not taking ourselves too seriously. It&#39;s about providing amazing people with an amazing experience so they can concentrate on their careers here, not their resumes. Sound good? Let&#39;s get down to some details...</p>
<p>
&nbsp;</p>
<p>
<strong>You:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Will research and implement an HRIS system to maintain employment data and track changes on an on-going basis</li>
<li>
Have experience maintaining employee personnel files in compliance with applicable laws and requirements</li>
<li>
Will develop and conduct our new employee orientation program&nbsp;</li>
<li>
Have managed open enrollment and all aspects of on-going benefits administration</li>
<li>
Will ensure legal compliance by monitoring and implementing applicable Federal and NY State employment regulations and maintaining supporting documentation&nbsp;</li>
<li>
Are disturbingly detail-oriented, unusually dependable, exceptionally efficient and know that while HR is serious business, you don&#39;t have to be serious all the time (no...seriously)</li>
<li>
Are prepared to manage all administrative aspects of employee processes, including: hiring, on-boarding, promotions, terminations, exit interviews, leaves of absence, salary administration and benefits changes</li>
<li>
Will manage our employee performance evaluation process&nbsp;</li>
<li>
Are looking to join a team that is truly engaging, fulfilling, energetic, sometimes whacky and always passionate</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>We:&nbsp;</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Don&#39;t mind carrying a case of Red Bull up 10 flights of stairs, covering the phones or steaming a couple of suits to help out a co-worker</li>
<li>
Currently use a PEO, so bonus points if you have prior experience using one</li>
<li>
Don&#39;t believe in fire drills (except literal ones - they save lives) but understand that sometimes things need to happen quickly and on short notice</li>
<li>
Are so excited to hear from you!</li>
</ul>
